Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
writeSdpFile(25.10)                                        writeSdpFile(25.10)

Name
       writeSdpFile  -  Saves  the  current SDP relative placement information
       into a file

Syntax
       writeSdpFile

       [-help]

       -file <file_name>

       [-template | -topGroup <group_name>]

       [-template | -command]

       [-template  | [-updateRelativePlaceConstraint | -updateOrientation]]

       Saves the current SDP relative placement information into  a  file.  By
       default, the output is in .sdp format. writeSdpFile enables you to save
       SDP  relative information so it can be reloaded in another Innovus ses-
       sion.

       The writeSdpFile command can be run any time after SDPs have  been  de-
       fined.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each writeSdpFile parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man writeSdpFile.

       -command
              Specifies that the  relative  placement  information  should  be
              saved in TCL commands format instead of .sdp format.

       -file <file_name>
              Specifies  the  name  of the output file containing SDP relative
              information.

       -template
              Specifies that the file should be saved as a  template  in  .sdp
              format.

              Note: This parameter cannot be used with -command or -topGroup.

       -topGroup <group_name>
              Indicates  that  the  relative placement information of only the
              specified SDP group should be written.

       -updateOrientation
              Updates the orientation of SDP instances before writing them  to
              the SDP file.

       -updateRelativePlaceConstraint
              Updates  relative  placement  constraints of SDPs before writing
              out the SDP file. Use this parameter to write  out  the  updated
              SDP/TCL  file  after any change in SDP relative placement due to
              placeDesign  or  manual  changes.  The  -updateRelativePlaceCon-
              straint  option  can be used with the -command and -topGroup op-
              tions as well.

Examples
              * The following command writes the current  SDP  information  in
                SDP format in a file named test.sdp:

                writeSdpFile -file test

              * The  following command writes the SDP information for the sdp-
                GrpA group in the SDP TCL command format to  the  output  file
                output.sdp.

                writeSdpFile -file output.sdp -command -topGroup sdpGrpA

